value.0: A man who looks worse for wear. His shoulders are sagged, making him appear shorter than he really is, and dark bags line the skin under his eyes. He jumps at any loud noise and can be seen often looking over his shoulder. The clothing he wears is new but the articles are far too big for his skinny frame.
This young woman looks like she could collapse at any moment. At times she stares at nothing and one can only wonder what it is she is seeing or reliving.

Unlike many of the hostel guests, this man does not appear to be depressed or worse. If anything he comes off as incredibly angry, always muttering obscenities to himself when he thinks no one can hear him. He dresses the part of a huntsman with a leather tunic covering most of his body and a warm cloak wrapped about his shoulders.

The one in charge of making the meals for those who reside in the hostel. He seems to take his job very seriously, knowing the battle against starvation rides on his shoulders. At times his hands shake uncontrollably.

Uphold true and fitting justice and maintain the spirit of the law, not the letter of the law. Fitting recompense will always accrue for one's actions. Violence will meet violence and evil pay back evil, but good will also come to those who do good. Walk the line of the Doombringer's teachings, seeking retribution, but do not fall into the trap of pursuing evil acts for evil's sake, for that way is seductive and leads only to one's downfall. Vengeance must be sought for all injustices, and all punishments must fit the crime. Revenge is sweetest when it is sharpened with irony. All attacks must be avenged. Those who do not respond to attacks against their person or that which they hold dear only invite future attacks.

Locals can be seen kneeling here from time to time, adding a line to the lists. If one pages through what has been written, they find that it is no simple ledger, but an accounting of wrong-doings and slights, recorded here at the feet of the idol, in the hopes that the Lord of the Three Thunders (or one of his agents) will see them...
